archimate:DataObject.name: PartyRevShareReconDiscrepancy
archimate:DataObject.documentation: A difference between information received from another party with the revenue share determined by an enterprise that is to be resolved. For example; an enterprises calculated revenue share for a product offering may be missing a product that has been acquired that appears on an bill/invoice from another party. Note: This entity is related to two of any combination of PartyPayment; PartyPaymentItem; ComponentShareProdOfferItem; AppliedPartyBillingRate.
